## PHP Data Types

PHP supports different types of data to store values.

## Types of Data

String  → Text
Integer → Numbers without decimal
Float   → Decimal numbers
Boolean → true / false
Array   → Multiple values
Null    → No value
Object  → Complex data


### Example

<?php
$name = "Sdr";           // String
$age = 21;               // Integer
$price = 10.5;           // Float
$isStudent = true;       // Boolean

var_dump($name);
var_dump($age);
var_dump($price);
var_dump($isStudent);
?>

